10 SPF cats were subjected to FIV infection with the highly virulent GL8 strain. Expression levels of feline IFNα were compared in whole blood samples collected from the cats immediately before and 1 week after FIV challenge infection. 9 out of 10 cats displayed higher IFNα expression after infection. An average of 2.4-fold induction in expression of this cytokine could be measured in the cats after infection (p
 = 0.0059) (Fig. 4
).
